body: Hi @christthi , the converted model looks good. Did you try running on CPU? And could you please provide the input data that you use?

Hi @yufenglee, running it on the CPU works fine. Sorry, I should added this information in the question.

The input data is a camera live stream. My example image is a dalmatiner, which my model (running on the CPU or using a different inference engine) classify correct. Here the example image.
![Test](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/75883699/139381764-fb3c5520-500d-4137-a85a-62c239625efe.png)
. 

Thanks for your help.

So you are implementing your own execution provider: OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_VsiNpu? If CPU EP works correctly, then the glue code should be fine. Then it looks like the implementation of VsiNpu EP has issue?

This is the nxp provider for using the NPU on the I.MX8M plus. Yes, everything works fine using the CPU Ep. The VSI NPU Ep works fine for float models too. Only for quantized models I get wrong results. I also get wrong results when I use the NNAPI execution provider. So maybe something is wrong with my code. Could you please check that?
@gwang-msft , could you please help to check?

If you are using NNAPI EP, and on Android API level 29+, please try this option,

https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/3f5c1e1c58939c0de30e232ea0ef0c30644166b0/include/onnxruntime/core/providers/nnapi/nnapi_provider_factory.h#L41-L46

With this option (available on Android API level 29+ only), you can force the NNAPI to run on CPU fallback (nnapi-reference), if the result is correct with this option on, then the issue may be caused by the driver of the NPU

This issue has been automatically marked as stale due to inactivity and will be closed in 7 days if no further activity occurs. If further support is needed, please provide an update and/or more details.
